h1. install pg + gem

keywords: instal ubuntu 10.10 postgreSQL with pg gem
"source":http://solyaris.wordpress.com/2008/08/09/setup-postgres-in-ubuntu/

??sudo aptitude install postgresql

#setup postgres user
$ sudo su postgres -c psql template1
template1=# ALTER USER postgres with PASSWORD 'password';
template1=# \q


sudo apt-get install pgadmin3??

and now the gem 

??sudo apt-get install postgresql-client libpq5 libpq-dev
sudo gem install pg??

... before that I also runned  @$ sudo apt-get install ruby-dev build-essential@ but donno if that had any effect for the funcionality 

Everytihng works.. however if you run @@rake db:creat@@ and get 
??FATAL:  Ident authentication failed for user "postgres"?? 
or similar, than you have to modify @/etc/postgres/8.2/main/pg_hba.conf@ and change:
??localhost   all   all   ident sameuser??
to
??localhost   all   all   md5??
note: I also had to change same way line @@local   all  postgres  indent@@


restart postgresql 
?? sudo /etc/init.d/postgresql restart??

h2. usefull comands for pg

Creating a new PostgreSQL user 
@$ sudo -u postgres createuser -d -R -P <new username>@

Removing a PostgreSQL user 
@$ sudo -u postgres dropuser <usernamen>@

#Create a new database owned by <username>
@$ sudo -u postgres createdb -O <usename> <database name>@


















h1. installing ruby 1.9.2 on ubuntu 10.10

"source of information":http://excid3.com/blog/2010/10/ruby-on-rails-3-and-mysql-on-ubuntu-10-10/

??sudo apt-get install ruby-full

wget production.cf.rubygems.org/rubygems/rubygems-1.3.7.tgz

tar -xvf rubygems-1.3.7.tgz

cd rubygems-1.3.7/

sudo ruby setup.rb

sudo ln -s /usr/bin/gem1.8 /usr/bin/gem

sudo gem install rdoc

sudo gem install rails??

